  "description": "The script configures a GEOS-Chem model run based on user-supplied options, adjusting various configuration files like AGCM.rc, CAP.rc, and gcm_run.j to match the selected settings. The script supports different runtime environments like NCCS, NAS, JIBB, and DESKTOP, allowing the configuration to adapt to specific site requirements. It also handles various options for atmospheric and ocean resolutions, restart types, and boundary conditions. Notably, the script can activate features like RRTMG radiation schemes, single-moment microphysics, and Wavewatch III (WW3) integration. It also provides the functionality to link restarts from specific directories based on the selected resolution and restart type. The script also enables the use of minimal boundary datasets, facilitating smaller, faster experiments. Lastly, it configures the script to enable the use of Hyper-Q for GPU acceleration and policeme for model monitoring."
